living in the UK. Dmitry, I am Richard. Nice to meet

00:17:14.000 --> 00:17:21.989
you. Dmitry Skarga says he oversaw the transfer of the yacht from

00:17:22.000 --> 00:17:29.989
Abramovich to Putin. In March 2002 in Amsterdam, there was a

00:17:30.000 --> 00:17:33.989
representative of Mr Abramovich. Skarga says the yacht was given to

00:17:34.000 --> 00:17:45.989
an offshore company but the real owner was President Putin.

00:17:46.000 --> 00:18:05.989
We have seen documents that would appear to support Skarga's story.

00:18:06.000 --> 00:18:08.989
Roman Abramovich's lawyers said the claims were unsubstantiated, little

00:18:09.000 --> 00:18:14.989
more than a rehash of speculation and rumours. But they didn't

00:18:15.000 --> 00:18:21.989
specifically deny that he had given President Putin a yacht.

00:18:22.000 --> 00:18:27.989
You can hardly blame Abramovich for wanting to keep on Putin's good

00:18:28.000 --> 00:18:38.989
side. Standing up to him can be dangerous.

